SIMPLE: pelt
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pelt
<hw>Pelt</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧lt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>pelz</ets> a pelt, fur, fr. OF. <ets>pelice</ets>, F.
<ets>pelisse</ets> (see <er>Pelisse</er>); or perh. shortened fr.
<ets>peltry</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The skin of a beast with the
hair on; a raw or undressed hide; a skin preserved with the hairy or
woolly covering on it. See 4th <er>Fell</er>.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Raw <qex>pelts</qex> clapped about them for their clothes.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The human skin.</def> <mark>[Jocose]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Falconry)</fld> <def>The body of any quarry killed
by the hawk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pelt rot</b></col>, <cd>a disease affecting the hair or
wool of a beast.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pelt
<hw>Pelt</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pelted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pelting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>pelten</ets>,
<ets>pulten</ets>, <ets>pilten</ets>, to thrust, throw, strike; cf. L.
<ets>pultare</ets>, equiv. to <ets>pulsare</ets> (v. freq. fr.
<ets>pellere</ets> to drive), and E. <ets>pulse</ets> a beating.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To strike with something thrown or driven; to assail
with pellets or missiles, <as>as, to <ex>pelt</ex> with stones;
<ex>pelted</ex> with hail.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The chidden billows seem to <qex>pelt</qex> the clouds.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To throw; to use as a missile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My Phillis me with <qex>pelted</qex> apples plies.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pelt
<hw>Pelt</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To throw
missiles.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To throw out words.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Another smothered seems to <qex>pelt</qex> and swear.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Pelt
<hw>Pelt</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A blow or stroke from something
thrown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelta</ent>⟦br⟧
